{
  "texts": [
    "In other words, risk tolerance can trigger an implicit coordination process.",
    "As one non-risk-lover tells us, it makes more sense to explore when they are now highly likely to collectively uncover the diamond: This means the number of risk-lovers would need to grow less than proportionally to produce enough exploration, a prediction we can later test in the laboratory.",
    "Next, we try introducing pro-sociality.",
    "This time, we run the baseline streetlight experiment with pro-social agents, starting with one pro-social agent (out of the five players) and incrementing until all five AI agents are pro-social.",
    "We tell the primed agents they are only successful if the others choose the diamond, which means they should try to generate information that gives the group the best chance of discovering a diamond."
  ]
}